- cs.WEB (Web Technologies) is also likely as the paper deals with webpage loading process and optimization. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the study uses Internet Retailer Top 500 websites as a dataset. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is possible as the paper mentions the "visualComplete" event, which could be related to multimedia content. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the study involves crowdsourcing and analyzing user behavior.
